thread.title: Dolphins left tackle Branden Albert inactive for game against Jets
thread.title_full: Dolphins left tackle Branden Albert inactive for game against Jets | CP24.com

author: The Associated Press
title: Dolphins left tackle Branden Albert inactive for game against Jets
text:
LONDON -- Miami Dolphins left tackle Branden Albert was inactive for Sunday's game against the New York Jets at Wembley Stadium in London.
Albert had been doubtful this week because of an injured left hamstring. Jason Fox will replace Albert in the lineup.
For the Jets, backup linebacker Jamari Lattimore was also inactive. Lattimore had been listed as doubtful while being evaluated for a concussion.
Also, Jets linebacker Trevor Reilly was active. Reilly missed the Jets' game against Philadelphia last Sunday with a badly infected finger.
Guard Willie Colon (knee), tight end Jeff Cumberland (concussion), wide receiver Chris Owusu (knee) and cornerback Darrin Walls (hamstring) remain out.
Dolphins backup tight end Dion Sims was ruled out Friday with a concussion.
